HOUSE RESOLUTION 191
By Lafferty
A RESOLUTION to commend Makayla Paris for exemplary
service as a legislative intern.
WHEREAS, each legislative session, the members of this legislative body are pleased to
recognize certain persons who have committed themselves, through their adroit service, to the
betterment of the legislative process; and
WHEREAS, Makayla Paris is one such individual, who has distinguished herself in her
role as a legislative intern for Representative Justin Lafferty; Ms. Paris's work has resulted in
innumerable benefits for the legislators she assisted and the General Assembly as a whole; and
WHEREAS, born in Ripley, Ms. Paris spent most of her life in Chattanooga but has lived
across the State, gaining a deep understanding of various Tennessee families, lifestyles, and
values; and
WHEREAS, Makayla Paris is a student at the University of Tennessee, Knoxville, where
she is pursuing a Bachelor of Arts degree in Public Affairs with a concentration in National
Security; during her collegiate career, she has served as an ambassador for the Howard H.
Baker, Jr., School of Public Policy and Public Affairs; and
WHEREAS, she has a deep passion for public service and continues to engage in
experiences that are centered on serving others; after her internship with the legislature, she will
begin a position with Big Brothers Big Sisters as a statewide policy strategist; and
WHEREAS, eager to familiarize herself with the characteristics and complexities of
Tennessee State government and to further her studies, Makayla Paris brought her many
abilities and singular expertise to Capitol Hill for the 2026 session of the One Hundred
Fourteenth General Assembly; and
HR0191
017520
- 1 -

WHEREAS, throughout the 2026 legislative session, Ms. Paris has surpassed all criteria
that define a devoted and conscientious legislative intern; and
WHEREAS, Makayla Paris has performed her many duties with extraordinary insight
and rare decorum; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, that we commend
Makayla Paris for outstanding service as a legislative intern for Representative Justin Lafferty
and extend to her our best wishes for every future success.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy.
